.flex-container {
  /* use the flex display property */
  display: flex;

  /* control the direction of elements within the container */
  flex-direction: row;

  /* control how elements wrap within the container */
  flex-wrap: nowrap;

  /* align items along the cross axis vertically */
  align-items: center;

  /* align items along the main axis horizontally */
  justify-content: center;
}
```

You can then use this class in your HTML by adding the class to a container element, like so:

```html
